Senator Daniel
1 moves to amend the bill on page 1, line 4, by inserting the following at the end of the line and
2 before the period:
3 "AND TO REQUIRE THE ATTORNEY GENERAL TO SUBMIT A REPORT REGARDING
4 VIOLATIONS OF G.S. 14-277";
5
6 and on page 1, lines 19-20, by rewriting the lines to read:
7 "SECTION 2. No later than June 1, 2025, the Attorney General shall submit a report
8 to the Joint Legislative Oversight Committee on Justice and Public Safety containing the
9 following information to the extent the information is available:
10 (1) How many convictions for violations of G.S. 14-277 have been obtained from
11 January 1, 2021 through March 1, 2025.
12 (2) How many convictions for violations of G.S. 14-277 obtained from January
13 1, 2021 through March 1, 2025 were based on the defendant's impersonation
14 of an agent of the Immigration and Customs Enforcement of the United States
15 Department of Homeland Security.
16 The Attorney General shall request the required information and coordinate the required
17 response by requesting information from all necessary parties, including but not limited to the
18 North Carolina Administrative Office of the Courts, the North Carolina Conference of District
19 Attorneys, and any elected district attorney.
20 SECTION 3. Section 1 is effective when it becomes law and applies to actions filed
21 or commenced on or after that date. The remainder of this act is effective when it becomes law.".
